1
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:31,850
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,190 --> 00:01:34,910
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:36,229 --> 00:01:36,880
Honey,

4
00:01:37,229 --> 00:01:38,490
I'm going out for a bit.

5
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:42,070
Officer Li called yesterday
and asked me to come over today.

6
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:44,789
I guess there might be some new progress
in Leilei's case,

7
00:01:44,789 --> 00:01:45,509
or

8
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,280
maybe Ding Zhibo's.

9
00:01:47,789 --> 00:01:49,990
I'll grab some groceries on my way home.

10
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:18,870
Honey.

11
00:02:24,190 --> 00:02:25,000
I'm back.

12
00:02:29,430 --> 00:02:31,160
Why are you sitting in the dark?

13
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:39,010
Did you ever work as a private tutor
when you were in college?

14
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,150
Yes, I did.

15
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
You know
what my family situation was like.

16
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
I had to earn my own living expenses.

17
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,770
Did you ever tutor a student

18
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:55,600
whose mother was named He Xiao?

19
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:00,470
Why bring her up?

20
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:02,170
Who told you about her?

21
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,120
Officer Li met with me today.

22
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:09,030
I thought it was about Leilei

23
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:10,470
or Ding Zhibo,

24
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,020
but it was neither.

25
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,090
He told me

26
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,260
that the student said

27
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:22,160
his mother, He Xiao,
abandoned her family for you

28
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,960
and then committed suicide.

29
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:28,210
He remembered your name is Luo Liang.

30
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,470
He Xiao,

31
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:33,310
just like Leilei,
who committed suicide for Xia Yi,

32
00:03:33,310 --> 00:03:34,910
was a victim of gaslighting.

33
00:03:36,470 --> 00:03:37,530
Officer Li said...

34
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,910
the one who put together
the complete PUA Theory

35
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:43,370
goes by the name "Mister."

36
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:46,070
He's extremely good at reading people—

37
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:48,520
an absolute professional.

38
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,000
Why are you

39
00:03:53,590 --> 00:03:54,720
telling me all this?

40
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,060
Because they think

41
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:58,650
you

42
00:03:59,079 --> 00:04:00,320
are Mister.

43
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,650
Do you believe that?

44
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,740
I don't want to believe it.

45
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,690
But that's what they think.

46
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:14,400
They said that in 2007,

47
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,190
you were studying
at Tianfu Medical University,

48
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:18,720
and that's when you worked as a tutor.

49
00:04:19,269 --> 00:04:20,470
I've told you before,

50
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,370
if you want to leave,

51
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:24,070
you can do so anytime.

52
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:26,000
You know exactly

53
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,400
where our marriage certificates are kept.

54
00:04:32,790 --> 00:04:33,670
Tell me,

55
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:35,740
is what they said true?

56
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,040
Alright.

57
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,370
I did know He Xiao,

58
00:04:44,930 --> 00:04:46,820
and I did tutor her son.

59
00:04:47,380 --> 00:04:49,580
She indeed left a deep impression on me.

60
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:56,050
But it wasn't a pleasant one.

61
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:05,780
He Xiao

62
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:07,550
was also from Diannan.

63
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,720
Since we were from the same place,

64
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,240
she was very warm toward me

65
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,630
when we first met.

66
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,970
Her husband was rarely at home,

67
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,390
and her son was disobedient

68
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:18,790
and did poorly in school.

69
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,360
At that time,

70
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,160
I simply felt she had a hard life.

71
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:27,580
So occasionally, I'd help out
with heavy chores around the house.

72
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,730
She really liked watching movies.

73
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,020
One time when I went to her house,

74
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,630
she said her son had gone to
a classmate's house,

75
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:36,560
so the lesson would have to be canceled.

76
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,750
But then she said,

77
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,040
since I was already there,

78
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,970
she'd still pay me for the session,

79
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,540
as long as I stayed the full two hours,

80
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:45,270
like a normal class.

81
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,250
Of course, I agreed.

82
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,920
I was a poor student back then.

83
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,450
I wanted to earn that money.

84
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:54,980
Later, she asked me

85
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,210
to watch a newly released movie with her,

86
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:00,280
called "The Reader."

87
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,240
I've seen that movie.

88
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:11,160
It's about
a young woman and a teenage boy.

89
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,070
Right.

90
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:13,680
In that movie,

91
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:14,900
there's a scene

92
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,600
where the two of them
are sitting in the bathtub reading.

93
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,200
She said, since I was a tutor,

94
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,800
she wanted me to read to her.

95
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:22,800
She had chosen "The Red and the Black"

96
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,070
and "Anna Karenina."

97
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,040
Both books

98
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:30,480
deal with secret affairs and infidelity.

99
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:33,810
So you and she...

100
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,320
How could I possibly do that?

101
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,120
You know what I've been through.

102
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,360
I would never let myself

103
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:42,290
get into that kind of
compromising situation again.

104
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:46,190
I left without even collecting
the tutoring fee that time.

105
00:06:46,190 --> 00:06:47,650
I quit on my own after that.

106
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:51,230
That's it?

107
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,390
That's it.

108
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:58,680
As for what you said—
that she later had an affair

109
00:06:58,680 --> 00:06:59,630
and abandoned her family—

110
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:01,430
that doesn't surprise me at all.

111
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,220
She was still young back then.

112
00:07:03,610 --> 00:07:06,140
Living like a grass widow
must've been tough.

113
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,160
But I have no idea who she

114
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,290
had the affair with.

115
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:12,920
And you just said
she took her own life later.

116
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,180
I'm sorry to hear that,

117
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,450
but I know even less about that.

118
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,600
You said

119
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,310
those cops think I'm...

120
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,000
"Mister"?

121
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:29,040
Killing people
through romantic manipulation?

122
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:30,650
I think that's absurd.

123
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,830
Look at you.

124
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,040
Aren't you still alive and well?

125
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:43,800
Come on.

126
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:45,680
Let it go.

127
00:07:58,390 --> 00:07:58,920
Alright.

128
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,570
I shouldn't have said this.

129
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:08,090
That Officer Li...

130
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,210
once came to see me

131
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,510
as a patient.

132
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:17,070
He has PTSD.

133
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,300
It's highly likely

134
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,240
that he's being sidelined at work.

135
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,390
He's desperate to solve a big case

136
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,720
and transfer out of that precinct.

137
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,270
I don't know the exact reason,

138
00:08:26,270 --> 00:08:27,670
but what I can be sure of is

139
00:08:27,870 --> 00:08:30,330
that he's in a very unstable state
right now.

140
00:08:31,070 --> 00:08:33,330
He sees everyone as a potential suspect.

141
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,270
If you don't believe me,

142
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:40,080
you can go to the hospital
with me tomorrow.

143
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:42,390
I'll have the nurse pull up his records
from that day for you,

144
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,550
so he won't be able to deny it
when you confront him.

145
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:45,210
Afterward,

146
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,870
if he reports me
for breaching his medical privacy

147
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:48,790
and I lose my job over it,

148
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:49,790
I won't blame you.

149
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,870
It's just a job.

150
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:54,540
It's not as important as
earning your trust.

151
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,090
I really despise those people.

152
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,480
If they believe I committed a crime,

153
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,240
they can just present evidence
and arrest me.

154
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,910
But sneaking around behind my back,
whispering to my wife,

155
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:10,440
trying to drive a wedge between us—

156
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,100
what kind of behavior is that?

157
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:14,880
If you think you've been wrongly accused,

158
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,960
you can go to Officer Li
to clear your name

159
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,740
and let them investigate you.

160
00:09:20,630 --> 00:09:21,630
Why should I?

161
00:09:22,030 --> 00:09:23,600
And how am I supposed to clear my name?

162
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,840
You just said it yourself—

163
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:25,840
that's simply what they think!

164
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,040
What can I do about it?

165
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,040
Just like you—

166
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,270
you had no way to clarify the matter

167
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:30,200
with Ding Zhibo!

168
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,240
You didn't want to explain!

169
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,840
You felt it would just be humiliating!

170
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,300
Isn't that the same for me?

171
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,340
This is absurd.

172
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,140
Look me in the eyes

173
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:43,870
and tell me—

174
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,550
are you "Mister"?

175
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,030
I'm not.

176
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:54,320
I'll say it again.

177
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,200
I. Am. Not.

178
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:10,360
I believe.

179
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:13,870
I believe you.

180
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:18,630
I believe you.

181
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:21,900
You're not.

182
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:24,300
You're not.

183
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:28,630
Mom...

184
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,360
Zishan.

185
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:30,910
Mom...

186
00:10:31,850 --> 00:10:32,870
Mom is here.

187
00:10:32,930 --> 00:10:34,360
Tell me—who is he?

188
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:36,360
Zishan.

189
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:37,720
Mom!

190
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:39,080
Mom...

191
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,620
Mom will protect you.

192
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:41,030
No.

193
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:41,550
Tell me.

194
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:47,080
Don't... Don't...

195
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,750
Don't go.

196
00:10:48,430 --> 00:10:49,830
Don't go looking for him.

197
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:50,720
Him?

198
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,150
Who is he?

199
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:53,720
No...

200
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:55,510
Zishan, who is he?

201
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,270
Who is he, Zishan?

202
00:10:59,270 --> 00:10:59,750
No...

203
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:03,400
Is the man Luo Liang?

204
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:04,630
Zishan?

205
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,390
Liang...

206
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,270
Zishan?

207
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:07,200
Liang...

208
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,720
Is it Luo Liang?

209
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:09,740
Liang!

210
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:13,180
Fire...

211
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:14,950
Fire... Fire!

212
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:16,960
Together!

213
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,460
Go to hell!

214
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:19,960
Let go of him!

215
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,440
I'm the one who wants to be with him!

216
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,280
Go away!

217
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,670
His feelings for you are not love!

218
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:26,150
You can't be with him!

219
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,130
-Let go of me!
-Not unless I'm dead!

220
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,470
Let go of Luo Liang!

221
00:11:32,430 --> 00:11:34,150
-Mom, Mom, no!
-Zishan!

222
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:35,480
Mom!

223
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,790
-No!
-Zishan, calm down!

224
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:37,480
Mom!

225
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:38,790
Mom!

226
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:39,370
Mom!

227
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,570
-How could she be like this?
-Zishan!

228
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:42,770
Calm down, Zishan!

229
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,000
What's wrong?

230
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:47,510
Zishan, calm down!

231
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:49,310
I'm sorry, Mom! Mom!

232
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:49,720
Mom,

233
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,460
get up!

234
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:52,040
I'm sorry!

235
00:11:52,310 --> 00:11:52,790
Mom,

236
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:53,510
I'm sorry!

237
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,620
Mom!

238
00:11:54,910 --> 00:11:55,360
Mom!

239
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:56,550
Mom!

240
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:58,920
Help!

241
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:00,800
Zishan...

242
00:12:04,950 --> 00:12:05,550
No.

243
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,830
We can't continue.

244
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:14,290
This memory is too painful for her.

245
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:17,320
She would rather remain
in her delusion forever

246
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,050
than face it again.

247
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:21,460
For her, moments of lucidity

248
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,670
are actually a form of suffering.

249
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:29,370
Doctor? Doctor!

250
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,240
H-How is my daughter?

251
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,860
She's undergoing hypnotherapy.

252
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:33,840
Try not to worry too much.

253
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,440
Then, when can I take her home?

254
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,360
She can't eat or sleep properly here.

255
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,760
Here's the thing: the police are
still conducting an investigation.

256
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,790
Besides, you and she aren't related,

257
00:12:42,790 --> 00:12:44,270
so we can't let you take her back.

258
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:46,240
She's in a very unstable state right now

259
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,030
and needs intervention and treatment

260
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:50,030
from professional psychiatrists.

261
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,180
Dr. Lin!

262
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:55,790
Coming.

263
00:14:09,270 --> 00:14:09,790
Hello.

264
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:12,750
How's the person I asked you

265
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,670
to check on?

266
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,090
Wasn't she admitted to the ICU?

267
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,000
Even in the ICU, some patients get better,

268
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,010
and some don't.

269
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:23,010
There seem to be police at the hospital.

270
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:25,340
I don't want to bring trouble upon myself.

271
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,050
That's true.

272
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:32,670
Thank you.

273
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:35,790
Come on.

274
00:14:39,270 --> 00:14:40,200
It's too stuffy

275
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,240
in the ward.

276
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:44,100
I want to take her downstairs
for some fresh air.

277
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,650
Is that okay?

278
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,270
We'll be right back up.

279
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:50,960
Be quick about it.

280
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,080
Okay, okay.

281
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,000
Thank you.

282
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,010
Let's go.

283
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:05,870
Hurry up.

284
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:12,790
[Accessible Restroom; Women]

285
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:08,640
Let's go.

286
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:30,790
Ma'am.

287
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:32,570
You're here.

288
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:33,740
Here you go.

289
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:34,690
Okay.

290
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:35,570
Thank you.

291
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,900
Being discharged?

292
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,130
Yes, recovered.

293
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:44,030
How much is this?

294
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:44,560
One yuan.

295
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:45,550
Here.

296
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:46,550
Okay.

297
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,410
Your accent doesn't sound local.

298
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,810
Where is your hometown?

299
00:15:51,630 --> 00:15:52,440
Diannan.

300
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:54,820
Thank you.

301
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:55,690
No problem.

302
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:05,100
[Dialing]

303
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:16,740
[Son]

304
00:16:22,730 --> 00:16:24,340
Did he ever tell you

305
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:27,240
that taking too much of this medicine
can kill you?

306
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:29,510
Just keep this firmly in your mind!

307
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,630
Not a single day can be missed,

308
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:31,960
and not a single pill can be skipped!

309
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,840
Feed the medicine to her
exactly as I said.

310
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:34,600
Not a single day missed,

311
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,660
and not a single pill skipped, got it?

312
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,180
Sorry.

313
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:53,080
The number you have dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

314
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,410
Please try again later.

315
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,110
[Ringing]

316
00:16:55,110 --> 00:16:55,730
[Dialing]

317
00:16:58,630 --> 00:16:59,910
Hello. Where to?

318
00:17:01,170 --> 00:17:02,720
The long-distance bus station.

319
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,320
Okay.

320
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:19,099
[Saturday, July 20, 2019]

321
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:44,470
Your cooking is getting better and better.

322
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:46,350
Eat more if you like it.

323
00:17:49,650 --> 00:17:54,110
[Welcome to Nanhuguan Service Area]

324
00:17:54,150 --> 00:17:57,180
[Restaurant] [Supermarket]
[Mother & Baby Room] [Toilet]

325
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:59,400
Let me wipe your hands for you.

326
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:00,380
That one...

327
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:02,460
Don't scratch.

328
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:03,790
Don't scratch. Be good!

329
00:18:03,790 --> 00:18:04,190
Let me.

330
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,360
Alright. Let's go.

331
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,500
Come on. Let's go.

332
00:18:10,530 --> 00:18:11,480
Watch your step.

333
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:11,880
Right.

334
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:12,960
Watch your step.

335
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:13,780
Good.

336
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:14,830
Good.

337
00:18:14,850 --> 00:18:15,450
Very good.

338
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:17,280
Let's go. Our bus is over there.

339
00:18:18,070 --> 00:18:19,250
Go home with Mom.

340
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:21,210
Go back to our Diannan.

341
00:18:19,610 --> 00:18:23,190
[Restaurant] [Supermarket]
[Mother & Baby Room] [Toilet]

342
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:23,750
Sweet and delicious Sugar-Oil Fritters!

343
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:26,560
Soft and sticky, Nanhu's local specialty!

344
00:18:27,030 --> 00:18:29,240
Don't miss it when you pass by!
Take a look!

345
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,190
Hungry, huh?

346
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:32,210
I have food in the bag.

347
00:18:34,550 --> 00:18:35,960
You really want to eat that?

348
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,920
[Tanhua Local Snacks; Sweet, Soft,
Crispy Outside, and Tender Inside]

349
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,480
Thank you.

350
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:39,640
-Come again if you like it!
-Is it this one?

351
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:40,970
Is this the one you want?

352
00:18:41,350 --> 00:18:42,170
Sure thing!

353
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:43,570
I'll pack it for you.

354
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:44,820
Take care.

355
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,550
Ma'am.

356
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:47,300
What are these?

357
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:48,240
These?

358
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,160
These are Sugar-Oil Fritters,

359
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,480
a specialty of our Nanhu.

360
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:51,450
Taste great.

361
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:53,830
-One order, please.
-Want some?

362
00:18:53,830 --> 00:18:54,860
To Tanhua!

363
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:56,830
Any passengers going to Tanhua?

364
00:18:56,830 --> 00:18:57,510
We're leaving now!

365
00:18:57,510 --> 00:18:59,490
Any passengers going to Tanhua?

366
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:00,910
[Xiangtang] [Tanhua]

367
00:18:59,830 --> 00:19:00,690
We're leaving!

368
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:02,920
To Tanhua!

369
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:06,810
To Tanhua! Any passengers going to Tanhua?

370
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,470
My daughter's favorite.

371
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:09,350
Okay.

372
00:19:09,350 --> 00:19:11,000
Auntie, I'll have one order too.

373
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:11,740
Coming right up!

374
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:12,410
How much?

375
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:13,240
Fifteen yuan.

376
00:19:14,030 --> 00:19:14,350
Okay.

377
00:19:14,350 --> 00:19:15,350
Here's the money.

378
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:17,210
Thank you.

379
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:19,220
Are you going to Tanhua?

380
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:26,880
[Xiangtang] [Tanhua]

381
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,620
This is the bus.

382
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:23,520
Are there still passengers

383
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,350
going to Tanhua?

384
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:25,280
Any passengers?

385
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:26,700
We're leaving now!

386
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:27,720
Okay.

387
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,500
Zishan.

388
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:31,720
Zishan!

389
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,400
Zishan!

390
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:42,220
Fire!

391
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:43,830
No!

392
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:45,030
Mom!

393
00:19:45,030 --> 00:19:46,030
No!

394
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:51,470
It's so tragic.

395
00:19:52,820 --> 00:19:56,280
It turns out Qiao Zishan accidentally
killed her mom herself.

396
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:58,350
No wonder she had a mental breakdown.

397
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,160
Does that match the autopsy report?

398
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:02,560
Yes, it does.

399
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,960
Back then, I contacted
the Harbor Island police

400
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:07,000
and had them scan a copy
of the autopsy report.

401
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:07,930
The record shows

402
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:11,270
Qiao Lihua's body did have injuries
consistent with a fall.

403
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:14,840
This drawing is so pretty.

404
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,820
This girl looks a lot like you.

405
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:18,910
Who is the boy?

406
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,720
I can't tell you.

407
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:25,470
He said I can't tell anyone yet.

408
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:27,770
I have to wait

409
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,680
until Mom agrees.

410
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:33,200
So...

411
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:36,480
just because Qiao Lihua
didn't approve of them being together,

412
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:37,480
Qiao Zishan...

413
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:39,730
accidentally killed her?

414
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:44,550
I keep feeling it's not that simple.

415
00:20:56,310 --> 00:20:58,310
Have some hot milk to help you sleep.

416
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,040
Thank you.

417
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,240
It's my fault.

418
00:21:03,110 --> 00:21:04,070
Because of me,

419
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:05,700
you're worried again.

420
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,440
Don't say that.

421
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:13,340
We're family.

422
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:23,170
Hello, who is this?

423
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:25,240
Su!

424
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,200
Something urgent came up at the hospital.

425
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,260
I need to head over.

426
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:52,200
Hello, Ms. Yan. What's wrong?

427
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,350
He got a phone call

428
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:55,510
and then rushed out.

429
00:21:55,790 --> 00:21:58,940
When he left,
he even took his phone charger.

430
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:00,900
He usually wouldn't

431
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:04,300
take things like that
when he works overtime at the hospital.

432
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:07,590
And... the caller was a woman,

433
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,640
and she called him "Su."

434
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,850
I wonder if it might be his mother.

435
00:22:13,110 --> 00:22:14,040
Ms. Yan, Ms. Yan,

436
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:15,890
you should leave there quickly.

437
00:22:15,890 --> 00:22:17,240
You're acting like an undercover now.

438
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,240
This isn't right.

439
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:19,960
Gathering evidence

440
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:20,960
and bringing him to justice

441
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,400
is literally our job.

442
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:26,960
He has surveillance cameras
installed in the house.

443
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:27,890
He must have seen

444
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:29,720
you guys coming to me.

445
00:22:33,170 --> 00:22:38,440
[Stop]

446
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:55,850
Car rental documents.

447
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:02,530
If the police come to you,

448
00:23:02,530 --> 00:23:04,390
just say you were feeling very low

449
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:06,160
and rented a car to kill yourself.

450
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,830
I talked you out of it after we met.

451
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,780
But my car suddenly broke down
when I was about to leave.

452
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:10,880
I urgently needed a vehicle,

453
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:11,740
so I took yours.

454
00:23:12,150 --> 00:23:14,200
Other than that, you don't know anything.

455
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,060
What happened?

456
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,200
Remember what I said.

457
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,000
Don't slip up.

458
00:23:33,590 --> 00:23:34,460
You just said

459
00:23:36,070 --> 00:23:36,930
that Luo Liang

460
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,360
has been taking care of that crazy girl.

461
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:41,440
Yes.

462
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:44,070
That girl admitted

463
00:23:44,070 --> 00:23:45,790
that she accidentally killed her mom

464
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:47,000
in the fire back then.

465
00:23:47,970 --> 00:23:50,680
Mister closed
the Amusement Park shortly after.

466
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:51,880
Maybe the tragedy was so horrific

467
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:53,210
that it made him flinch.

468
00:23:56,750 --> 00:23:59,180
If Luo Liang really is "Mister"—

469
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:03,110
someone who didn't care about
all those girls taking their own lives—

470
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:05,570
would he really be rattled
by one more death?

471
00:24:05,790 --> 00:24:08,680
If that girl was truly brainwashed
by him into

472
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:11,090
killing her own mother with her own hands,

473
00:24:11,590 --> 00:24:13,240
I think he'd be proud of it,

474
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:14,150
wouldn't he?

475
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:16,200
So,

476
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:20,180
there was another reason
the Amusement Park was shut down?

477
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,340
I'm going back.

478
00:24:24,090 --> 00:24:26,620
Although he said
he wouldn't come back today,

479
00:24:26,750 --> 00:24:28,480
what if he suddenly comes back?

480
00:24:28,830 --> 00:24:29,650
Okay, okay.

481
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:30,960
Ms. Yan, be careful.

482
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:31,790
Be very careful.

483
00:24:31,790 --> 00:24:33,720
Call me if anything happens, okay?

484
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,400
I'm at the door.

485
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,780
I cut the fuse to the camera.

486
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:02,550
The camera shouldn't be working now.

487
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:03,950
Come open the door for me.

488
00:26:12,590 --> 00:26:14,070
I've checked several times.

489
00:26:14,070 --> 00:26:15,590
Still just those eight cameras,

490
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:17,050
all in the same positions.

491
00:26:45,590 --> 00:26:46,590
He's so sick.

492
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,000
No normal person

493
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:52,730
would install so many cameras
in their own house.

494
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,970
Why are you still staying here?

495
00:27:01,750 --> 00:27:02,880
I don't know either.

496
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:04,350
What do you mean you don't know?

497
00:27:04,350 --> 00:27:05,240
Just move out immediately

498
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,510
and divorce him.

499
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:11,480
Right now, I'm the person closest to him.

500
00:27:14,310 --> 00:27:15,640
If he really is that man,

501
00:27:17,110 --> 00:27:18,630
and if he slips up,

502
00:27:19,510 --> 00:27:21,510
I'm the only one who might notice it.

503
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,070
Wait,

504
00:27:25,830 --> 00:27:27,000
are you the police?

505
00:27:28,110 --> 00:27:30,310
Why are you locking horns with a psycho?

506
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:32,320
What if one day he snaps?

507
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,850
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

508
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:36,720
He won't.

509
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:41,270
He doesn't get satisfaction
from killing people.

510
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:42,920
K-Killing people?

511
00:27:44,070 --> 00:27:46,030
I'm telling you, I don't agree with this.

512
00:27:46,030 --> 00:27:47,070
I can't let Jiale

513
00:27:47,070 --> 00:27:48,400
grow up without his mom.

514
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:52,590
How is Jiale?

515
00:27:54,270 --> 00:27:55,200
He's doing fine.

516
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,280
When I get back, I'll tell him

517
00:27:58,310 --> 00:27:59,510
not to believe a single word

518
00:27:59,510 --> 00:28:00,750
that lunatic said.

519
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,350
No, please don't.

520
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:05,740
He's still young,

521
00:28:06,510 --> 00:28:07,550
just a child.

522
00:28:08,830 --> 00:28:10,290
If Luo Liang contacts him,

523
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:15,280
and Jiale accidentally lets
something slip, that would be trouble.

524
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:17,000
Okay.

525
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:19,020
I'll listen to you.

526
00:28:21,270 --> 00:28:22,000
Don't worry.

527
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:24,530
I won't let our son
get caught up in any of this.

528
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:30,640
You should head back now.

529
00:28:32,070 --> 00:28:34,510
Even though he said
he wouldn't be back tonight,

530
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:35,370
what if he does?

531
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:39,790
You're really stubborn.

532
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,210
No matter what happens,

533
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:45,640
tell me immediately.

534
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:49,450
This time, I'm sticking with you
no matter what.

535
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:37,800
Hello?

536
00:29:38,070 --> 00:29:40,270
We just received a report
from Wuzhou People's Hospital,

537
00:29:40,270 --> 00:29:41,510
saying Qiao Zishan is missing.

538
00:29:41,510 --> 00:29:43,030
Hua Sanmei secretly took her away.

539
00:29:43,030 --> 00:29:44,160
We checked the surveillance footage

540
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,640
and the taxi driver's statement,

541
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:48,020
which show they got on
a long-distance bus to Diannan.

542
00:29:48,020 --> 00:29:49,790
Have you arranged to intercept them?

543
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:50,400
We notified the checkpoints

544
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:52,660
and had the bus stopped at a toll station.

545
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:53,920
But they weren't on the bus—

546
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,590
only Hua Sanmei's travel bag was.

547
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:57,370
Her phone was inside it.

548
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,400
Okay, got it.

549
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:04,870
Let's go to my station.

550
00:30:04,870 --> 00:30:05,930
It's very close by.

551
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:09,710
Luo Liang's birthday...

552
00:30:15,130 --> 00:30:16,250
[Incorrect password. Please try again.]

553
00:30:20,070 --> 00:30:21,750
Xiao Su's birthday.

554
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:23,680
1981-

555
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,200
01-18.

556
00:30:27,330 --> 00:30:28,610
[Incorrect password. Please try again.]

557
00:30:33,590 --> 00:30:34,070
Master.

558
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:36,440
Look at you guys,

559
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:39,570
turning the station
into a special investigation unit.

560
00:30:40,980 --> 00:30:41,260
[Incorrect password. Please try again.]

561
00:30:41,500 --> 00:30:42,150
[Incorrect password. Please try again.]

562
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:46,500
The day the Amusement Park launched.

563
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:48,920
Officer Li said it was...

564
00:30:50,540 --> 00:30:51,890
[Password hint: Luo Liang]

565
00:30:50,870 --> 00:30:53,450
0102...

566
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,060
Chief Hu,

567
00:30:59,090 --> 00:31:00,310
no records were found
of Luo Liang purchasing plane

568
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:01,310
or train tickets.

569
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:01,970
Chief Hu,

570
00:31:02,310 --> 00:31:03,830
we haven't been able to
locate Luo Liang's phone.

571
